    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Lupus is the Garou’s natural wolf form, allowing them to fully embrace their animal instincts.</p><p>In this form, a Garou blends seamlessly into the wild, gaining heightened awareness of the natural world and strong ties to spirits and the Umbra.</p><p>Lupus form favors instinct, perception, and spiritual connection over raw force or social interaction.</p><p>While in Lupus (Wolf) form, you gain the following benefits and limitations.</p><p>Speed: 50 feet</p><p>Benefits:</p><p>• You have advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks.</p><p>• You have advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on smell.</p><p>• Bite: 1d6 + Strength modifier (piercing).</p><p>• Claw: 1d4 + Strength modifier (slashing).</p><p>Limitations:</p><p>• You can’t wield manufactured weapons or use items requiring hands.</p><p>• You can attempt to communicate in humanoid languages at disadvantage (DC 10).</p><p></p>",
      "chat": "<p>While in Lupus (Wolf) form, you gain the following benefits and limitations.</p><p>Speed: 50 feet</p><p>Benefits:</p><p>• You have advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks.</p><p>• You have advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on smell.</p><p>• Bite: 1d6 + Strength modifier (piercing).</p><p>• Claw: 1d4 + Strength modifier (slashing).</p><p>Limitations:</p><p>• You can’t wield manufactured weapons or use items requiring hands.</p><p>• You can attempt to communicate in humanoid languages at disadvantage (DC 10).</p><p></p>"
